Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Some interesting talk going on here: https://github.com/zcash/zips/pull/247

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> TLDR: Zcash and Hush don't quite see eye-to-eye on the future of memo field stuff, NO SURPRISE!

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Zcash is optimized for financial xtns, Hush is optimized for communicating. It makes sense

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> There are low-level things that will be designed differently, because of this divergence in design

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Zcash will only support 64KB memos, and so that means many low level changes from Hush, who will support 200KB or larger

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Privatoshi> HUSH could support nSPV, whereas ZCash has little to no mobile presence

Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[dscrd-hush] <Privatoshi> I know it is avoided for good reasons.
But people use cell phones, more than anything.
Would if instead of Signal, which has been doing some things that show a lack of respect for privacy, people use HUSH

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Hush has nSPV support already, we just haven't built it out yet. and nSPV is evolving very fast still
